      "explanation_en": "Momentum investing means buying stocks that have been rising in price, based on the idea that strong recent performance tends to continue in the near term. Traders use indicators like RSI (Relative Strength Index) and MACD to confirm when a stock has genuine upward momentum versus just a random spike. Today's decisions relied entirely on momentum scores \u2014 buying AMZN and YSS because their technical signals all point to sustained upward pressure.",
